co.cask.coopr.spec.template

Class ClusterTemplate

  • java.lang.Object
    • co.cask.coopr.spec.NamedEntity
      • co.cask.coopr.spec.BaseEntity
        • co.cask.coopr.spec.template.AbstractTemplate
          • co.cask.coopr.spec.template.ClusterTemplate

  • public final class ClusterTemplate
extends AbstractTemplate
    A cluster template defines different types of clusters that will be available for users to create. Templates define a set of services that are allowed to be placed on the cluster plus some service and layout constraints that will be used to determine which services to place on which nodes, and what hardware and images to use. A cluster template also specifies the full set of configuration key values that are needed on the cluster.
